  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Recent evidences suggest that obstructive sleep apnea (OSA) can contribute to cardiovascular
      disease even in the absence of hypertension. However, there are few data regarding the impact
      of OSA on the preHypertension and Masked Hypertension in apparently normotensive patients
      with OSA as well as the impact of treatment with continuous positive airway pressure.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
